@dev The address of the sibling contract that is used to implement the sooper-sekret

@dev An array containing the Doge struct for all Doges in existence. The ID
  of each doge is actually an index into this array. Note that ID 0 is a negadoge,
  the unDoge, the mythical beast that is the parent of all gen0 doges. A bizarre
  creature that is both matron and sire... to itself! Has an invalid genetic code.
  In other words, doge ID 0 is invalid... ;-)

@dev The Pregnant event is fired when two doges successfully breed and the pregnancy
  timer begins for the matron.

 @param _id The ID of the doge of interest.

Birth(address,uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.details: The Birth event is fired whenever a new doge comes into existence. This obviously  includes any time a doge is created through the giveBirth method, but it is also called  when a new gen0 doge is created.

Pregnant(address,uint256,uint256,uint256.details: The Pregnant event is fired when two doges successfully breed and the pregnancy  timer begins for the matron.

params._addr: The address that will be able to sire with your Doge. Set to  address(0) to clear all siring approvals for this Doge.
params._sireId: A Doge that you own that _addr will now be able to sire with.

bidOnSiringAuction(uint256,uint256).details: Completes a siring auction by bidding.  Immediately breeds the winning matron with the sire on auction.

params._matronId: - ID of the matron owned by the bidder.
params._sireId: - ID of the sire on auction.

params._matronId: The ID of the Doge acting as matron (will end up pregnant if successful)
params._sireId: The ID of the Doge acting as sire (will begin its siring cooldown if successful)

params._matronId: The ID of the proposed matron.
params._sireId: The ID of the proposed sire.

createGen0Auction(uint256).details: Creates a new gen0 doge with the given genes and  creates an auction for it.

createPromoDoge(uint256,address).details: we can create promo doges, up to a limit. Only callable by COO

params._genes: the encoded genes of the doge to be created, any value is accepted
params._owner: the future owner of the created doges. Default to contract COO

createSaleAuction(uint256,uint256,uint25.details: Put a doge up for auction.

createSiringAuction(uint256,uint256,uint.details: Put a doge up for auction to be sire.  Performs checks to ensure the doge can be sired, then  delegates to reverse auction.

params._id: The ID of the doge of interest.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

giveBirth(uint256).details: Looks at a given Doge and, if pregnant and if the gestation period has passed,  combines the genes of the two parents to create a new doge. The new Doge is assigned  to the current owner of the matron. Upon successful completion, both the matron and the  new doge will be ready to breed again. Note that anyone can call this function (if they  are willing to pay the gas!), but the new doge always goes to the mother's owner.

params._matronId: A Doge ready to give birth.

returns._0: The Doge ID of the new doge.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

isPregnant(uint256).details: Checks whether a doge is currently pregnant.

params._dogeId: reference the id of the doge, any user can inquire about it
reference the id of the doge, any user can inquire about it

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

setAutoBirthFee(uint256).details: Updates the minimum payment required for calling giveBirthAuto(). Can only  be called by the COO address. (This fee is used to offset the gas cost incurred  by the autobirth daemon).

setGeneScienceAddress(address).details: Update the address of the genetic contract, can only be called by the CEO.

params._address: An address of a GeneScience contract instance to be used from this point forward.

setSaleAuctionAddress(address).details: Sets the reference to the sale auction.

setSiringAuctionAddress(address).details: Sets the reference to the siring auction.

unpause().details: Override unpause so it requires all external contract addresses  to be set before contract can be unpaused. Also, we can't have  newContractAddress set either, because then the contract was upgraded.

withdrawAuctionBalances().details: Transfers the balance of the sale auction contract to the DogeHero contract. We use two-step withdrawal to prevent two transfer calls in the auction bid function.

doges.details: An array containing the Doge struct for all Doges in existence. The ID  of each doge is actually an index into this array. Note that ID 0 is a negadoge,  the unDoge, the mythical beast that is the parent of all gen0 doges. A bizarre  creature that is both matron and sire... to itself! Has an invalid genetic code.  In other words, doge ID 0 is invalid... ;-)

geneScience.details: The address of the sibling contract that is used to implement the sooper-sekret  genetic combination algorithm.

saleAuction.details: The address of the ClockAuction contract that handles sales of Doges. This  same contract handles both peer-to-peer sales as well as the gen0 sales which are  initiated every 15 minutes.

sireAllowedToAddress.details: A mapping from DogeIDs to an address that has been approved to use  this Doge for siring via breedWith(). Each Doge can only have one approved  address for siring at any time. A zero value means no approval is outstanding.

siringAuction.details: The address of a custom ClockAuction subclassed contract that handles siring  auctions. Needs to be separate from saleAuction because the actions taken on success  after a sales and siring auction are quite different.

approveSiring(address,uint256).notice: Grants approval to another user to sire with one of your Doges.

autoBirthFee().notice: The minimum payment required to use breedWithAuto(). This fee goes towards  the gas cost paid by whatever calls giveBirth(), and can be dynamically updated by  the COO role as the gas price changes.

breedWithAuto(uint256,uint256).notice: Breed a Doge you own (as matron) with a sire that you own, or for which you  have previously been given Siring approval. Will either make your doge pregnant, or will  fail entirely. Requires a pre-payment of the fee given out to the first caller of giveBirth()

canBreedWith(uint256,uint256).notice: Checks to see if two doges can breed together, including checks for  ownership and siring approvals. Does NOT check that both doges are ready for  breeding (i.e. breedWith could still fail until the cooldowns are finished).  TODO: Shouldn't this check pregnancy and cooldowns?!?

getDoge(uint256).notice: Returns all the relevant information about a specific doge.

giveBirth(uint256).notice: Have a pregnant Doge give birth!

isReadyToBreed(uint256).notice: Checks that a given doge is able to breed (i.e. it is not pregnant or  in the middle of a siring cooldown).

unpause().notice: This is public rather than external so we can call super.unpause  without using an expensive CALL.
